    "descripcionEn": "Schizophrenia is a chronic and severe psychiatric disorder that affects how a person thinks, feels, and behaves, causing a disconnection from reality. It is characterized by episodes of psychosis including hallucinations, delusions, and disorganized thinking, along with negative symptoms such as flat affect and social withdrawal. It affects approximately 1% of the world population and typically manifests between ages 16 and 30, with a profound impact on the individual's functional capacity. With adequate and continuous treatment, many people achieve stabilization and lead meaningful lives within their community.",
